title: Peeps into the Past: The echoes of Ancient Egypt in Haslemere
description: This December marks just over a century since one of the most breath-holding moments in archaeological history — the day in 1922 when Howard Carter first gazed into the long-sealed tomb of Tutankhamun. When his patron, Lord Carnarvon, asked nervously if he could see anything, Carter’s reply entered legend: “Yes, wonderful things.”
